    "plan_content": "Here's the full implementation plan I've built after thoroughly analyzing the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add Stepper Compound Component\n\n### Files to touch (4 total, no existing components modified)\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | **Create** |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | **Create** |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` | **Append** 1 entry before closing `]` (line 705) |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` | **Append** 1 entry before closing `]` (line 2651) |\n\n---\n\n### Architecture: Two React contexts (carousel.tsx pattern)\n\n**`StepperContext`** â€” shared by all descendants:\n```ts\n{ activeStep: number, orientation: \"horizontal\" | \"vertical\" }\n```\n\n**`StepperItemContext`** â€” shared by children of `StepperItem`:\n```ts\n{ step: number, state: \"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\" }\n```\n\n---\n\n### Component breakdown\n\n| Component | Element | data-slot | Key logic |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `Stepper` | `<div>` | `stepper` | Provides both contexts; `flex flex-col gap-4`; `data-orientation` |\n| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | `stepper-item` | Computes `state` from `step` vs `activeStep`; provides `StepperItemContext` |\n| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | `stepper-trigger` | Reads `step`+`state` from item context; shows `{children ?? step}`; 3-way styling |\n| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | `stepper-title` | Pure wrapper |\n| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | `stepper-description` | Pure wrapper |\n| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | `stepper-separator` | Reads orientation from `StepperContext`; reads state from `StepperItemContext`; `bg-primary` when completed, `bg-border` otherwise |\n| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | `stepper-content` | Returns `null` if `step !== activeStep` |\n\n---\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n1. **`StepperSeparator` lives inside `StepperItem`** â€” this is how it accesses state from context without needing a `step` prop (which the spec excludes). When step N is \"completed,\" its separator turns primary, visually connecting to step N+1.\n\n2. **`Stepper` root is `flex flex-col`** â€” for horizontal steppers, the user wraps `StepperItem`s in a `div className=\"flex items-center\"` in their layout. This lets `StepperContent` panels appear naturally below the indicator row while still being inside `<Stepper>` for context access.\n\n3. **No third-party deps** â€” pure React context + Tailwind, mirrors carousel.tsx pattern exactly. Registry entry has no `dependencies` field.\n\n4. **`registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]`** in the example entry, since the demo uses both.\n\n---\n\n### Verification steps\n1. `pnpm tsc --noEmit` in `apps/v4/` â€” no TypeScript errors\n2. Visual: clicking Next/Previous updates step states and content panels correctly\n3. Separator color transitions primary â†” muted as steps complete/revert\n4. `git diff --name-only` shows exactly 4 files, no existing component touched",
